            "name": "Trained Animal",
            "subtype": "ability",
            "text": "The beast tamer fights alongside a trained animal ally of its level or lower, most likely a tiger. The animal has the standard number of actions, uses its normal stat block, and counts toward the encounter's XP budget normally.  \n The beast tamer can spend 1 action to gain the support benefit appropriate to its trained animal. Unlike for an animal companion, this doesn't require the animal to use any of its actions.",
